Vice President Yemi Osinbajo at the funeral of the late Governor of Oyo State, said that late Governor Adebayo Alao-Akala was an open minded politician, saying that he would be missed for his magnanimity and compassion.

Osinbajo stated that late Governor Alao-Akala served the interest of his people when he was in power and gave quality counsel to those who were around him.

Alao-Akala retired from the Nigeria Police before delving into politics.
